00:30:07,340 --> 00:30:11,340
but I'd like to think what are the consequences,

534
00:30:11,340 --> 00:30:14,340
if, big if, what I'm telling you is true,

535
00:30:14,340 --> 00:30:18,340
that life started in these hydrothermal vents,

536
00:30:18,340 --> 00:30:22,340
and they started there because the structure of these vents

537
00:30:22,340 --> 00:30:25,340
favours the reaction between hydrogen and CO2,

538
00:30:25,340 --> 00:30:28,340
the proton gradients across membranes or across barriers,

539
00:30:28,340 --> 00:30:30,340
because that's still how cells work.

540
00:30:30,340 --> 00:30:35,340
And cells now get their hydrogen from almost anywhere.

541
00:30:35,340 --> 00:30:37,340
So in photosynthesis, it splits water,

542
00:30:37,340 --> 00:30:40,340
and the hydrogen is extracted from water,

543
00:30:40,340 --> 00:30:43,340
and it's cobbled onto CO2 to make organic molecules.

544
00:30:43,340 --> 00:30:47,340
But the basic reaction is hydrogen reacting with CO2

545
00:30:47,340 --> 00:30:51,340
in oxygenic photosynthesis, where the waste product is oxygen.

