00:30:55,340 --> 00:30:58,340
You take the hydrogen out of it, you leave the sulfur behind,

549
00:30:58,340 --> 00:31:00,340
you cobble it onto CO2,

550
00:31:00,340 --> 00:31:02,340
or you're growing like a methanogen in the vent.

551
00:31:02,340 --> 00:31:04,340
The hydrogen is bubbling out of the ground,

552
00:31:04,340 --> 00:31:07,340
you simply cobble it onto CO2.

553
00:31:07,340 --> 00:31:11,340
Life all across Earth is based on the reaction

554
00:31:11,340 --> 00:31:13,340
between hydrogen and CO2.

555
00:31:13,340 --> 00:31:15,340
And we go round eating things,

556
00:31:15,340 --> 00:31:19,340
but we're entirely dependent on the primary producers,

557
00:31:19,340 --> 00:31:21,340
the plants and the bacteria,

558
00:31:21,340 --> 00:31:24,340
which are basically reacting hydrogen with CO2.

559
00:31:25,340 --> 00:31:28,340
Hydrogen and CO2 don't react

560
00:31:28,340 --> 00:31:32,340
except under these rather careful conditions,

561
00:31:32,340 --> 00:31:34,340
where you have structure,

562
00:31:34,340 --> 00:31:36,340
the same kind of structure that we see in cells.

563
00:31:36,340 --> 00:31:39,340
So how common are those conditions likely to be?

564
00:31:39,340 --> 00:31:42,340
On the early Earth, we think that they would have been

565
00:31:42,340 --> 00:31:45,340
basically all the way across the sea floor.

566
00:31:45,340 --> 00:31:48,340
Because it's a reaction between rock and water.

567
00:31:48,340 --> 00:31:52,340
So this is, if you imagine this is the sea floor,

568
00:31:52,340 --> 00:31:55,340
and then down beneath in the crust underneath the sea floor,

569
00:31:55,340 --> 00:32:01,340
these green rocks here are rich in minerals like olivine.

570
00:32:01,340 --> 00:32:04,340
So olivine is iron, magnesium rich rock,

571
00:32:04,340 --> 00:32:06,340
mostly found in the mantle of the Earth today,

572
00:32:06,340 --> 00:32:09,340
which is why you don't see so many reactions like this anymore,

573
00:32:09,340 --> 00:32:12,340
but four billion years ago there wasn't really such a difference

574
00:32:12,340 --> 00:32:14,340
between the mantle and the crust.

575
00:32:14,340 --> 00:32:17,340
So we think these reactions would happen almost everywhere.

576
00:32:17,340 --> 00:32:21,340
The water percolates down to depths of five or six kilometres

577
00:32:21,340 --> 00:32:25,340
beneath the crust, and will react with these rocks.

578
00:32:25,340 --> 00:32:27,340
So if you were to take a lump of olivine

579
00:32:27,340 --> 00:32:29,340
and put it in a bucket of water,

580
00:32:29,340 --> 00:32:32,340
you'd probably get one bubble in about a week's time.

581
00:32:32,340 --> 00:32:34,340
It's not something, you know,

582
00:32:34,340 --> 00:32:37,340
it's not an experiment you want to do for the kids.

583
00:32:37,340 --> 00:32:39,340
But at the higher temperatures and pressures

584
00:32:39,340 --> 00:32:41,340
down at the bottom of the sea floor,

585
00:32:41,340 --> 00:32:44,340
it really is bubbling with hydrogen gas.

586
00:32:44,340 --> 00:32:46,340
It's a pretty vigorous reaction.

587
00:32:46,340 --> 00:32:48,340
And that's really all it takes.

588
00:32:48,340 --> 00:32:51,340
It's the reaction between water and rock

589
00:32:51,340 --> 00:32:54,340
to produce strongly alkaline fluids rich in hydrogen gas.

590
00:32:54,340 --> 00:32:56,340
It's an exothermic reaction,

591
00:32:56,340 --> 00:32:58,340
which means it's producing heat,

592
00:32:58,340 --> 00:33:01,340
and so these are buoyant warm fluids which percolate back up.

593
00:33:01,340 --> 00:33:03,340
And when they get to the sea floor,

594
00:33:03,340 --> 00:33:06,340
they react with the waters of the ocean,

595
00:33:06,340 --> 00:33:09,340
the minerals in the ocean to precipitate as these vents.

596
00:33:09,340 --> 00:33:12,340
So the reaction between rock and water is down below the sea floor,

597
00:33:12,340 --> 00:33:15,340
but the vents themselves are up at the sea floor.

598
00:33:15,340 --> 00:33:19,340
So they should happen on any wet rocky planet.

599
00:33:19,340 --> 00:33:23,340
And there's actually quite a lot of lovely suggestions

600
00:33:23,340 --> 00:33:27,340
from across our own solar system that they do happen.

